description:
Clay County Habitat for Humanity Mission

Building safe, decent, and affordable housing in partnership with the community and God’s people in need.

About Clay County Habitat for Humanity

Clay County Habitat for Humanity is a nonprofit, ecumenical Christian housing ministry dedicated to eliminating substandard housing in Clay County area (Penney Farms, Green Cove Springs, Middleburg, Orange Park, Keystone Heights). As an affiliate of Habitat for Humanity International, we work in partnership with local families and volunteers to build safe, decent, and affordable homes for low-income individuals and families in need.

All are welcome

Clay County Habitat is an equal housing opportunity nonprofit. We do not discriminate against any person or family based on their race, color, religion, sex, age, handicap, family status, national origin, sexual orientation, or gender identity.

As a matter of policy, Habitat for Humanity International and its affiliated organizations do not proselytize. This means that Habitat will not offer assistance on the expressed or implied condition that people must either adhere to or convert to a particular faith or listen and respond to messaging designed to induce conversion to a particular faith.

Habitat for Humanity International Vision

A world where everyone has a decent place to live.

Habitat for Humanity International Mission Statement

Seeking to put God’s love into action, Habitat for Humanity brings people together to build homes, communities and hope.

About Habitat for Humanity International

Founded in Americus, Georgia, USA, in 1976, Habitat for Humanity today operates around the globe. In 2023, Habitat for Humanity helped 13.4 million people build or improve a place to call home. An additional 9.5 million people gained the potential to improve their housing conditions through training programs and advocacy work driven by Habitat in local communities.

name: Brave Health
description:
Brave Health is a fully virtual behavioral health clinic offering psychiatric medication management, individual and group therapy for patients 13+. 

We're in-network with most Florida State health plans, including Medicaid and Medicare, and most commercial plans making access easier for patients. 

Who we treat: Clinical Pathways or Workflows include:  Adolescents 13+ years of age, Serious Mental Illness, Chronic Illness patients, Maternal Mental Health through PMAD certified clinicians, Seniors and a separate workflow for Assisted Living & Homebound Patients, Co-Occurring SUD (Substance Use Disorders), Families & Teen in Foster Care, Families & Couples Counseling and more.

Our process is quick, easy and straightforward. We offer personalized recommendations and treatment plans for all patients who complete an assessment. We ensure that their first appointment is scheduled within days, with outreach beginning just hours after the referral is made.  

Our services include:

·  Therapy: Individual therapy with licensed therapists, including support for anxiety, depression, trauma, and other mental health concerns.

·  Group Therapy:  Over 40 therapy groups designed to help individuals cope with various mental health challenges and difficult life experiences. 

·  Medication management: Care provided by psychiatrists or nurse practitioners for patients requiring medication for mental health conditions.

·  Telehealth services: All care is provided through secure online platforms, making it convenient for patients to access care from home or anywhere.

description:
Operation Lifeline, Inc. is a nonprofit organization dedicated to fostering safe, stable, and inclusive housing with a special focus on serving veterans and low-income individuals and families. Based in Northeast Florida, we work at the intersection of housing, workforce development, and community support to help people build long-term stability and self-sufficiency.

Our mission is to break cycles of housing instability and economic hardship by providing affordable housing solutions, critical home repairs, accessibility modifications, and supportive services. Through permanent supportive housing initiatives, home rehabilitation programs, and community-based construction projects, we ensure that vulnerable populations have access to safe, dignified places to call home.
Operation Lifeline also invests in workforce development, particularly for transitioning service members through DoD SkillBridge and hands-on training programs in construction and nonprofit management. By creating real-world learning opportunities, we equip participants with marketable skills while strengthening our community infrastructure.

Guided by compassion, accountability, and service, Operation Lifeline partners with local governments, builders, volunteers, and funders to deliver measurable impact. Our work is rooted in the belief that housing is the foundation for health, stability, and opportunity—and that every person deserves a chance to thrive.

Fostering Safe, Inclusive Housing with a Focus on Veterans.
